In article <21642@oasys.dt.navy.mil> curt@oasys.dt.navy.mil (Curt Welch) 
asks about MD5 and the UNIX password algorithm.

Yes, MD5 is public domain, and yes, it would make an excellent
replacement for the UNIX password algorithm. One significant advantage
is that MD5 lets you use passwords of arbitrary length, instead of
being limited to 8 characters as in the present algorithm.

Phil
